  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d87\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dad \u0da9\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Three diesel ships within two weeks",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera, the Minister of Electricity and Energy, says that several ships carrying diesel stocks are scheduled to arrive in the island in the next two weeks.",
        "He said this at a press conference held in Colombo today. Thus, between 8-9 days after the arrival of a ship carrying 40000 metric tons of diesel of the Indian Coral Energy Company,",
        "A ship carrying 40,000 metric tons of diesel from Vitol will arrive between 11-14.",
        "He said that a diesel ship of the Indian Oil Company is scheduled to arrive in the island between the 15th and 17th.",
        "The minister also insisted that the money needed for this has been deposited in parts.",
        "Also, the minister said that money has already been deposited for obtaining 7500 metric tons of diesel from Ceylon Indian Oil Company."
      ],
